                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="rubrication">
                           <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                           <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                        </seg>
                        <desc>The word God is rubricated in the first three works; the word Mary is rubricated in the final two works. Occasionally, the word God is rubricated with two black and then two red letters (e.g., <locus target="#19r">fol. 19r</locus>)</desc>
                        <desc>Columetric layout of text: <locus target="#137r" facs="140">fols. 137r, </locus> (Ps. 148); <locus target="#138r #138v" facs="141 142">138r, 138v, </locus> (Ps. 150); <locus target="#149r #149v" facs="152 153">149r, 149v</locus> (tenth Biblical Canticle).</desc>
